reason: Doc B is superior due to its exceptional factuality, providing precise official citations (Federal Register, Congress.gov, White House, presidency.ucsb.edu) and verifying numerous interconnected executive orders and legislative efforts. Doc A's 'What the EO Does' section aligns more closely with the explicit mandates found in the official text. Both documents excel in their critical analysis and adherence to the requested structure and tone.
